HEADWORD: Rootcap
<hw>Root"cap`</hw> <pr>(r⟦oomac⟧t"k⟦acr⟧p`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A mass of parenchymatous cells which covers and
protects the growing cells at the end of a root; a pileorhiza.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

